{"name": "archive", "metadata": {"name": "Archive", "version": "0.3", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "http://code.google.com/p/python-archive/", "license": "LICENSE.txt", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Simple library that provides a common interface for extracting zip and tar archives.", "upload_time": 1328490840}, "documentation": ["# python-archive\n\nThis package provides a simple, pure-Python interface for handling various\narchive file formats. Currently, archive extraction is the only supported\naction. Supported file formats include:\n\n- Zip formats and equivalents: `.zip`, `.egg`, `.jar`.\n- Tar and compressed tar formats: `.tar`, `.tar.gz`, `.tgz`,\n  `.tar.bz2`, `.tz2`.\n\n## Example usage\n\nUsing the `Archive` class:\n\n```\nfrom archive import Archive\na = Archive('files.tar.gz')\na.extract()\n```\n\nUsing the `extract` convenience function:\n\n```\nfrom archive import extract\n# Extract in current directory.\nextract('files.tar.gz')\n# Extract in directory 'unpack_dir'.\nextract('files.tar.gz', 'unpack_dir')\n```\n\nNote that calling extract with `safe=True` will ensure that the archive is\nsafe prior to extraction: `UnsafeArchive` exception will be raised when\narchive contains paths which would be extracted outside of the target\ndirectory (e.g. absolute paths):\n\n```\n# Safely extract in directory 'unpack_dir'.\nextract('files.tar.gz', 'unpack_dir', safe=True)\n```\n\n## Similar tools\n\n- <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/patool/> - portable command line archive file\n  manager.\n- <http://pypi.python.org/pypi/gocept.download/> - zc.buildout recipe for\n  downloading and extracting an archive.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "archive", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "archive.extract", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "to_path", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "safe", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Unpack the tar or zip file at the specified path to the directory\nspecified by to_path."]}], "variables": [{"name": "archive.extension_map", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "archive.ArchiveException", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Base exception class for all archive errors."]}, {"name": "archive.UnrecognizedArchiveFormat", "bases": ["ArchiveException"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Error raised when passed file is not a recognized archive format."]}, {"name": "archive.UnsafeArchive", "bases": ["ArchiveException"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Error raised when passed file contains absolute paths which could be\nextracted outside of the target directory."]}, {"name": "archive.Archive", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "archive.Archive.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "file", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "archive.Archive._archive_cls", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "file", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "archive.Archive.extract", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "to_path", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "safe", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "archive.Archive.namelist", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "defau